# Phase 4: Token Store

## Goal
Build `internal/tokenstore` — a pluggable credential storage layer used by
OAuth-based getters and setters (Slack, Google Calendar, etc.) to persist and
retrieve access/refresh tokens.

## Interface

```go
// Store persists and retrieves opaque credential strings keyed by
// (service, key). Service is e.g. "slack" or "google_calendar";
// key is e.g. "access_token" or "refresh_token".
type Store interface {
    Get(service, key string) (string, error)
    Set(service, key string, value string) error
    Delete(service, key string) error
}
```

## Backends

### File backend (default)
- Stores tokens in a JSON file at `~/.config/status/tokens.json`
  (or the path from `FileStoreConfig.Path`)
- Format: `{"slack": {"access_token": "xoxp-...", ...}, ...}`
- Reads the file on every `Get`; writes the whole file on every `Set`/`Delete`
- Safe for single-process use; protected by an in-process mutex
- Unit tests: inject a `readWriter` interface (in-memory bytes.Buffer) — no
  real files

### DynamoDB backend
- Table schema: partition key `service` (S), sort key `key` (S), attribute
  `value` (S)
- Uses `aws-sdk-go-v2` (add to go.mod)
- Endpoint from `AWS_ENDPOINT_DYNAMODB` env var (falls back to
  `DynamoStoreConfig.Endpoint`, then AWS default)
- Credentials from the default AWS credential chain
- Unit tests: connect to DynamoDB Local via `AWS_ENDPOINT_DYNAMODB`
  (default `http://localhost:8000`); skip with `t.Skip` if unreachable
- Each test creates a uniquely-named table, deletes it in `t.Cleanup`

## Factory

```go
func FromConfig(cfg config.TokenStoreConfig) (Store, error)
```

